Program: Discovery
Title: Rebuilding New Orleans
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrz7j
Last Broadcast Date: 29 August 2006
A visit to New Orleans to see how the city is rebuilding its flood defence system. A report a year after Hurricane Katrina devastated the city and its surroundings. Presenter, Julian Siddle, talks to those rebuilding their lives in the city and the people investigating why the flood defences failed.